reut2-004.sgm, UNOFFICIAL STRIKE HITS ROTTERDAM GRAIN SECTOR, About 220 men in Rotterdam port'sgrain sector stopped work this afternoon in an unofficialprotest at the slow progress of negotiations over a new workpractice agreement, a spokesman for the port and transportunion FNV said.    Negotiations between the union and employers, which are dueto resume early next week, are currently stalemated with theunion refusing to accept sweeping changes in working hours andpractices in return for a 1.5 pct pay increase.    The FNV spokesman said the action did not yet have officialbacking, but added that next week matters might be different. Reuter&#3;
