reut2-004.sgm, DUTCH PORT UNION CALLS OFF GENERAL CARGO STRIKES, Dutch port and transport union, FNV,has called off the strikes against planned redundancies thathave hit Rotterdam port's general cargo sector for the pasteight weeks, strike leader Paul Rosenmuller told a massmeeting.    The decision followed yesterday's ruling by an Amsterdamcourt preventing the sector's employers continuing with currentplans for 350 redundancies this year until the court sits againon May 7, Rosenmuller told a meeting of the general cargosector's 4,000 workers today.    The court ruled the employers had made a mistake in thecomplicated legal procedure for obtaining official permissionfor the redundancies, and therefore could not proceed.    There is no need to continue the strikes for the moment nowthe immediate pressure of redundancies has been lifted

